{"first-name":"John","last-name":"Warren","email":"john.warren@member.ses.nsw.gov.au","phone":"0487898040","query-type":"training-product-development","message":"Hello,

I've been looking into the package for PUA60120 Advanced Diploma of Public Safety (Emergency Management) and the unit PUAOPE003 Manage the Public Information function at an Incident, and I'm curious as to why the unit doesn't have any prerequisites regarding the other Public Information Functions, such as Media, Social Media, Community Liaison, or Info and Warnings?

If someone can explain the thought process around this decision to help me understand it would be highly appreciated."}
